<h2 id="section-top">Teenage and young adult cancer services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1596">Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address">TYA office 6th Floor West<br/>0114 2265000</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent7b9ae86f3f70424289c5703bc721a356">
</div>
<p>The Teenage and Young Adult (TYA) cancer team and facilities exist to help young patients through their cancer treatment and to support them and their families/carers throughout their treatment and afterwards.
</p><p>TYA cancer care in Sheffield is provided by two NHS Trusts.</p>
<p><strong>Sheffield Children’s Hospital</strong> is a JACIE accredited bone marrow transplant centre providing treatment for a wide range of cancers and leukaemia’s affecting teenage patients aged 13-16 years old.  </p>
<p> Facilities include:</p>
<p>
</p><ul>
<li>A specialist haematology and oncology ward and dedicated outpatient clinic</li>
<li>Free bedside TV (including Sky Sports) and DVD library</li>
<li>Areas to make snacks and drinks, play games and a quiet room for study or rest</li>
<li>Dedicated Youth Room on Ward M2</li>
<li>Educational support is available and we are a designated examination centre</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Sheffield Teaching Hospitals</strong> has dedicated Teenage and Young adult cancer treatment facilities on two sites for patients aged 16 – 24 years old and both  include day care chemotherapy and outpatient facilities.</p>
<p><strong>Weston Park Hospital is one of only 3 specialist cancer hospitals in the UK. </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Teenage Cancer Trust funded unit with five single rooms, kitchen facilities, TV/games room and conservatory. A quiet room also available for patients</li>
<li>One of two UK centres caring for patients Gestational Trophoblastic isease, treating young people from the Midlands and North of England</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Royal</strong><strong> Hallamshire Hospital</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>4 bedded Teenage Cancer Trust Young Adult Unit on the haematology ward with a two bedded bay and 2 two single rooms. There is a small multi activities room solely for the use of Young adult patients</li>
<li>JACIE  Accredited bone marrow transplant centre </li>
</ul>
<p>All treatment is given by experienced cancer doctors and nurses in age appropriate facilities in partnership with patients, family and carers. All patients are allocated a key worker who will act as their primary contact point at all times.  </p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-thingsshouldknowmodule">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Things you should know</h3>
<p>You can bring your own night clothes, toiletries and items to individualise your bed space. Open visiting is available and a carer is welcome to  stay overnight if needed. Dining/shop facilities are available in all 3 hospitals, shops, cash points etc are close by.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-serviceteamsummary">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear"><h3><a href="/Services/hospitals/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=9615">Staff</a></h3>
<div id="imageContent3324b4dcd5b94d1db836a9a744e9e6e1">
</div>
<p>The TYA team in Sheffield offer support to patients aged 13-24 years of age and their carers. Cancer treatments vary from surgery, surgery plus chemotherapy and or radiotherapy and our team have a great deal of experienced in supporting patients through this difficult time. We aim to make the patients journey through their cancer treatment a comfortable as possible. We also work closely with other health professional groups such as physiotherapist, dieticians etc who can help work with you if you have any specific problems.</p><p><a href="/Services/hospitals/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=9615">Learn more about our staff</a></p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
